name: Anesthesia and Pain Management
content: DEPARTMENT: Anesthesia and Pain Management DESCRIPTION: The Anesthesia and Pain Management Department provides safe, effective anesthesia and comprehensive pain relief for surgical and medical procedures, ensuring patient comfort and safety from pre-op to recovery. SERVICES: Laparoscopic procedures, Physical therapy, Pain and sensation relief during procedures, Neuro anesthesia services, Postoperative care, Doctor of Anesthesiology and Pain Management, Angiography and radiology suite coverage, Expertise of anesthesiologists, Comprehensive pain management with medications and interventional techniques, Use of anesthetics to prevent discomfort during procedures, Effective pain relief during and after surgery, Expertise in anesthesiology and pain management FACILITIES: The intensivists at the Department of Anesthesiology are vigilantly involved with patients in the medical, surgical, and cardiothoracic intensive care units PROCEDURES: Comprehensive preoperative evaluation, including detailed medical history, medication review, and risk assessment to ensure optimal patient safety and surgical readiness, Personalized administration of general and regional anesthesia, carefully tailored to each patient's unique medical profile and surgical requirements, Continuous, real-time monitoring of vital signs and patient status throughout all surgical procedures, utilizing advanced monitoring technologies, Development and implementation of individualized pain management plans before, during, and after surgery, integrating multimodal strategies for maximum comfort, Application of state-of-the-art techniques for both acute and chronic pain management, including interventional procedures, nerve blocks, and physical therapy as appropriate, Precise calculation and administration of anesthesia dosages, taking into account procedure type, patient age, gender, body mass index (BMI), and other relevant factors, Provision of expert anesthesia care for a broad spectrum of surgeries, such as laparoscopic, neurosurgical, cardiac, thoracic, and obstetric procedures, Utilization of regional anesthesia to deliver targeted pain relief, minimizing systemic side effects and promoting faster recovery, Comprehensive perioperative care, including support in intensive care and high dependency units, to ensure seamless patient management across all stages, Patient-centered education and counseling regarding anesthesia options, pain management techniques, and necessary medication adjustments, Round-the-clock (24/7) availability of highly qualified anesthesia and pain management specialists for both emergency and elective procedures, Strict adherence to internationally recognized safety protocols, infection control measures, and quality assurance standards to minimize risks and complications, Active collaboration with multidisciplinary teams—including surgeons, nurses, and allied health professionals—to optimize patient outcomes and enhance recovery, Thorough postoperative care encompassing effective pain control, vigilant monitoring, and comprehensive support to facilitate enhanced recovery and patient satisfaction, Specialized anesthesia and pain management services for obstetric patients, including continuous labor analgesia and tailored support during childbirth DOCTORS: Dr. Abaid Ur Rehman, Dr. Hana Khurshid, Dr. Sabir Khan, Dr. Syed Mehmood Ali URL: content: DEPARTMENT: Fetal Medicine DESCRIPTION: The Department of Fetal Medicine at Hameed Latif Hospital provides specialized care for expectant mothers, including high-risk pregnancies. content: DEPARTMENT: Gastroenterology DESCRIPTION: The Gastroenterology Department at Hameed Latif Hospital specializes in diagnosing and treating digestive system and liver disorders, offering advanced procedures and expert care for a wide range of gastrointestinal conditions, SERVICES: The Gastroenterology Department at Hameed Latif Hospital provides comprehensive care for digestive and liver disorders using state-of-the-art diagnostic and therapeutic techniques., Our expert gastroenterologists specialize in treating all organs of the digestive system, including the stomach, intestines, pancreas, liver, gallbladder, and esophagus., We offer a wide range of procedures such as endoscopy, colonoscopy, ultrasound, and advanced imaging to accurately diagnose and manage gastrointestinal conditions., Specialized services include non-surgical obesity management, removal of stones from bile or pancreatic ducts, and stent placement for blocked ducts., Patients are encouraged to consult a gastroenterologist if they experience symptoms like persistent abdominal pain, unexplained weight loss, chronic diarrhea or constipation, blood in stool, difficulty swallowing, recurring acid reflux, jaundice, or other signs of liver dysfunction., Our gastroenterologists are highly trained medical doctors dedicated to the diagnosis and treatment of digestive and liver diseases. Please note that 'gastrologist' is a non-medical term sometimes used interchangeably, but the correct term is 'gastroenterologist.' FACILITIES: PROCEDURES: Comprehensive evaluation and treatment of digestive and liver-related conditions, including hepatitis, fatty liver disease, and cirrhosis., Use of advanced diagnostic tools such as endoscopy, colonoscopy, ultrasound, and imaging tests to assess the digestive tract, liver, and pancreas., Endoscopy: A minimally invasive procedure to visually examine the digestive tract and identify abnormalities., Colonoscopy: A detailed examination of the colon to detect polyps, cancer, or other issues., Ultrasound and imaging: Non-invasive techniques to detect abnormalities in the liver, pancreas, and other digestive organs., ERCP (Endoscopic Retrograde Cholangiopancreatography): For diagnosing and treating bile duct and pancreatic conditions., Intragastric balloon placement: A non-surgical procedure for obesity management., Stone removal from bile or pancreatic ducts and stent placement for blocked ducts., Esophageal stricture dilatation and achalasia dilation procedures., Polypectomies and foreign body removal from the digestive tract., Personalized, research-based treatment plans developed by a multidisciplinary team of gastroenterologists, technicians, and support staff., Management of chronic and acute digestive symptoms such as abdominal pain, unexplained weight loss, chronic diarrhea, constipation, blood in stool, difficulty swallowing, acid reflux, jaundice, and signs of liver dysfunction., Specialized care for both adult and pediatric patients with digestive and liver diseases., Patient-centered approach ensuring accurate diagnosis, effective treatment, and compassionate care using the latest medical advancements. name: Gynecology and Obstetrics
content: DEPARTMENT: Gynecology and Obstetrics DESCRIPTION: The Gynecology and Obstetrics Department at Hameed Latif Hospital offers advanced care for women’s health, including high-risk pregnancies, minimally invasive surgeries, infertility treatment, and 24/7 emergency services, SERVICES: Minor and major obstetric and gynecological procedures, Normal delivery, forceps delivery, and C-section, Gynecological laser treatment, Minimally invasive gynecological laparoscopic surgeries, Infertility treatment, Neonatal care, 24/7 gynecological emergency services, Diagnosis and management of menstrual disorders (e.g., heavy bleeding or irregular periods), Polycystic Ovary Syndrome (PCOS), Uterine fibroids and ovarian cysts, Endometriosis, Infections and pelvic inflammatory diseases (PID) FACILITIES: This unit ensures shorter recovery times, minimal pain, and the best cosmetic results, making Hameed Latif Hospital the best hospital in Lahore for gynecologist services, Our patient-centered approach ensures the health and well-being of mothers and their babies from the prenatal stage through postpartum, Rashid Latif Khan, MIGSU boasts a custom-designed operation theater equipped with the latest endoscopic surgical technology PROCEDURES: Minimally invasive gynecological laparoscopic surgeries (including diagnostic and operative laparoscopy), Hysteroscopic procedures (diagnostic and operative hysteroscopy), Normal vaginal delivery, forceps delivery, and cesarean section (C-section), Gynecological laser treatments, Infertility evaluation and treatment (including ovulation induction, IUI, and advanced reproductive techniques), Management and surgical treatment of uterine fibroids and ovarian cysts, Endometriosis diagnosis and minimally invasive management, Pelvic reconstructive surgery and treatment of pelvic organ prolapse, Surgical and non-surgical management of menstrual disorders, Comprehensive care for high-risk pregnancies and complicated obstetric cases, Oncological gynecological procedures (for uterine, cervical, and ovarian cancers), Minimally Invasive Gynecological Surgery Unit (MIGSU) procedures utilizing state-of-the-art endoscopic surgical technology DOCTORS: Dr. Maria Azad, Dr. Anam Rashid, Dr. Ulvina Khalid, Dr. Samina Haq, Dr. Rukhsana Manzoor, Dr. Rabia Wajid, Dr. Rabia Nafees, Dr. Rohina Gul, Dr. Memoona Ali, name: Nephrology & Dialysis
content: DEPARTMENT: Nephrology & Dialysis DESCRIPTION: Comprehensive diagnosis and treatment of kidney diseases, dialysis, hypertension, and electrolyte disorders by expert nephrologists using advanced technology at Hameed Latif Hospital, Lahore, SERVICES: Diagnosis and treatment of kidney and liver disorders, Management of hypertension and electrolyte disorders, Comprehensive care for acute kidney injury and chronic kidney disease, Glomerulonephritis management, Personalized dialysis treatment plans, State-of-the-art dialysis facility, Care for patients with end-stage renal disease, Prevention of further kidney damage, Multispecialty care for complex kidney-related conditions FACILITIES: Which Services Are Offered at the Nephrology & Dialysis Facility at Hameed Latif Hospital, Our state-of-the-art dialysis center in Lahore provides comprehensive care for patients with kidney diseases, including those in critical care settings, With a 12-bedded facility, including dialysis chairs, and bedside dialysis available in ICU beds, we ensure that every patient receives optimal care PROCEDURES: Dialysis: A life-sustaining procedure that removes waste products, toxins, and excess fluids from the blood when the kidneys are no longer able to function adequately. Our facility offers both hemodialysis and peritoneal dialysis, tailored to each patient's medical needs., Acute Kidney Injury (AKI) and Chronic Kidney Disease (CKD) Management: Comprehensive evaluation and treatment plans for patients with sudden or long-term kidney dysfunction, aiming to restore or preserve kidney function and prevent complications., Glomerulonephritis and Hypertension Treatment: Specialized care for inflammatory kidney conditions and high blood pressure, utilizing advanced diagnostics and evidence-based therapies., Electrolyte Disorder Correction: Diagnosis and management of imbalances in essential minerals such as sodium, potassium, and calcium, which are critical for overall health and kidney function., Renal Transplant Medicine: Pre- and post-transplant care, including patient evaluation, preparation, and ongoing management to ensure the best possible outcomes for transplant recipients., Multidisciplinary Consultations: Collaboration with specialists in cardiology, endocrinology, and other fields to address complex cases involving multiple organ systems., Personalized Dialysis Care: Individualized treatment plans for both routine and emergency dialysis, ensuring patient comfort, safety, and optimal health outcomes. DOCTORS: Dr. Fowad Shahzad, Dr. Tashbeeb Gulzar, Dr. Muhammad Aamer, Dr. Syed Arsalan Khalid URL: https://www.hameedlatifhospital.com/departments/nephrology//

content: DEPARTMENT: Pulmonology DESCRIPTION: The Pulmonology Department at Hameed Latif Hospital specializes in diagnosing and treating lung and respiratory diseases, including asthma, COPD, lung cancer, and fibrosis, with advanced technology and expert care, SERVICES: Bronchoscopy for examining the internal airways, Asthma management, Chronic obstructive pulmonary disease (COPD) treatment, Lung cancer care, Windpipe and bronchial obstructions management, Lung fibrosis treatment, Cystic fibrosis care, Cardiothoracic surgery, Tuberculosis treatment, Respiratory therapists, Dietician support, Management of interstitial lung disease FACILITIES: Our highly qualified pulmonology doctors provide exceptional care for a wide range of respiratory conditions using advanced techniques and equipment PROCEDURES: Comprehensive evaluation and management of respiratory diseases, including asthma, COPD, lung cancer, and interstitial lung disease, using evidence-based protocols., Advanced diagnostic procedures such as bronchoscopy, spirometry, and imaging to accurately identify and monitor lung conditions., Multidisciplinary care provided by a team of pulmonologists, respiratory therapists, nurses, physiotherapists, clinical pharmacologists, and nutritionists to ensure holistic treatment for every patient., Personalized treatment plans tailored to each patient's needs, ranging from medication management to interventional procedures and rehabilitation., Continuous monitoring and follow-up for chronic respiratory conditions to optimize patient outcomes and improve quality of life., State-of-the-art facilities and technology, combined with highly skilled specialists, make Hameed Latif Hospital a leading center for pulmonology care in Lahore. name: Urology and Lithotripsy
content: DEPARTMENT: Urology and Lithotripsy DESCRIPTION: The Urology and Lithotripsy Department at Hameed Latif Hospital offers advanced diagnosis and treatment for urinary tract and male reproductive disorders, including kidney stones, prostate issues, infertility, and minimally invasive lithotripsy, SERVICES: Calcium stones: Formed when excess calcium combines with other waste products., Struvite stones: Composed of magnesium, phosphate, and ammonia, may form after a urinary tract infection., Uric acid stones: May occur when urine is too acidic, such as in gout or malignancies., Cystine stones: Consist of cystine, a building block of muscles, nerves, and other parts of the body., Kidney Transplant Surgery, Prostate Surgery (TURP), Uro-Oncology (Kidney Cancer, Testis Cancer, Bladder Cancer, Prostate Cancer), Reconstructive Surgery (Pyeloplasty, Augmentation) FACILITIES: With a team of highly skilled urologists and state-of-the-art equipment, we are proud to be a leading center for urological services in Lahore PROCEDURES: Lithotripsy is a non-invasive medical procedure that uses focused shock waves to break kidney stones into smaller fragments, allowing them to pass naturally through urine., This procedure typically lasts 30–60 minutes, requires no incisions, and is associated with a faster recovery and lower risk of complications compared to traditional surgery., Lithotripsy is especially effective for stones larger than 5 mm that are too large to pass on their own, making it a preferred alternative for many patients., Most patients experience minimal discomfort during or after the procedure, and any mild pain is usually manageable with medication., At Hameed Latif Hospital, the Department of Urology and Lithotripsy offers advanced diagnostics and comprehensive treatments for kidney stones, bladder dysfunction, prostate issues, and infertility., Our team of highly skilled urologists has performed thousands of successful lithotripsy procedures, ensuring ethical practices, thorough donor-recipient screening, and dedicated follow-up care for long-term health., Lithotripsy is widely available in major hospitals across Pakistan, including Hameed Latif Hospital, which is equipped with state-of-the-art technology and a commitment to patient safety and excellence. DOCTORS: Dr. Jamil Rahim, Dr. Sabir, Dr. Ghulam Mujtaba Zafar, Brig. Dr. Muhammad Ramzan Ch, Dr. Farooq Malik, Dr. Khaliq Ur Rehman, Dr. Muzammil Tahir URL: https://www.hameedlatifhospital.com/departments/urology-and-lithotripsy/
